div.p:
And whatſoever elſe thou
knoweſt more uſeful or expedient
for me or any of thy ſervants:

If I take the wings of the morning,
and remain in the uttermoſt
parts of the Sea;

That we, being delivered out
of the hands of our enemies,
might ſerve him without fear;

Through the tender mercy of
our God, whereby the day-ſpring
from on high hath viſited us,

To thee all Angels cry aloud,
the Heavens, and all the Powers
therein;

I will ſay unto the Lord, Thou
art my hope, and my ſtrong hold;
my God, in him will I truſt.

The Lord himſelf is thy Keeper:
the Lord is thy defence upon
the right hand;

q.p:
Fear God, and keep his Commandments;
for this is the whole
duty of Man.

div.p:
How are they brought into deſolation;
As in a moment they
are utterly conſumed with terrors.
